JACKSON, Miss., June 1 — The Rev. Ralph David Aber nathy called on youg blacks tonight to avoid violence even in the face of provocation by the white authorities.

“Do not retaliate with vio lence,” the civil rights leader told a cheering crowd of 1,500 blacks at a rally. “Let them kill us—let our innocent blood cry out on their hands.”

It was Mr. Abernathy's first visit to Mississippi as the leader of the Southern Chris tian Leadership Conference. He came to lend his support to a boycott called by a group of black students and business men following the slaying of two young blacks by the police on the campus of Jackson State College last month.